snippet.textDisplay:
Best thing about a WRX is no nannying gizmos. It's one of the last, pure, simple rally cars for the road. The rev hang out of 1st gear is a bit annoying, but everything else is fantastic.


Can't say I understand the pricing strategy for the trims, though. I bought my base 2015 WRX new for under $27K USD, and never felt anything above the base model was worth the money. $35K for the "Limited" was ridiculous and I had to hunt for a base model. I nearly had a heart attack once I started seeing Civic Type R and even the old Focus RS selling for close to $40K.
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay:
@TheStraightPipes
Rev Hang is due to the weight of the Flywheel....
The heavier the flywheel the more "Rev Hang" a car will have due to the heavy weight spinning momentum (this also means it will rev slower).  
A Type R will have a lighter flywheel so revs drop faster once the clutch is engaged (the other side to this coin is the car revs quicker!!)  

WRX (heavier flywheel). vs STI
Civic, Civic SI... vs... Civic Type R (heavier to Lighter)
Cars in general get heavier flywheels because they are more drivable (less transmission chatter at idle and low RPM)
Car Engineering is difficult and they are rarely putting the time into the Manual transmissions anymore. PDK, Dual Clutch, and ZF transmissions are the future.....But..... (Save the Manuals)

-Side note AWD cars harder to launch (with manual transmission)(they like to bog down)(Also Subaru clutch release points are to high off the floor)
- It is great to see two friends doing what they have a passion for, keep up the reviews and dynamic together ....TheStraightPipes
